UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Alta Mae HOWARD, Appellee. No. 9821. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 22, 1941. See, also, 28 F.Supp. 985. J. Charles Dennis, U. S. Atty., of Seattle, Wash., and Francis J. McGan, Atty., Department of Justice, of Butte, Montana, for appellant. George C. Furber, of Seattle, Wash., for appellee.

Before DENMAN, MATHEWS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
